Tar'alan Bathhouse~
Though the archway to the east is broad enough to easily support a pair
of double doors, nothing more blocks the view of the world outside this
pleasantly warm room than a small chunk of quartz dangling from a single
hinge.  The small faceted fragment hints at the sheer beauty of the
long-gone portals when they were whole, its vibrant crimson hue a
brilliant contrast to the milky quartz of the building.  A small hole has
been carved into the northern wall, mimicking a window left open to the
world, allowing a view of the oft-used street.  A perfect square has been
hollowed out in the center of the floor, with three tall steps leading
down into a sullenly bubbling pit of gooey tar.  Though wisps of noxious
steam drift lazily upwards from the sticky liquid, it doesn't seem too
hot; in fact, the warmth is rather pleasant.  Tar oozes slowly from a
crack in the western wall of the chamber, languidly seeping into the
large bath.  Over the centuries, the tar has eaten away at the smooth
quartz wall, leaving it pockmarked with many crevices.
