Joxqoun Alley~
A sharp corner brings the tunnel to a ninety degree angle here, with a
small passageway leading south while an enormous cavern opens up towards
the west.  A string of ancient lanterns dangle from mounts on both walls,
though only those along the eastern side still cast their dancing
flickers of illumination.  A supply line for the lanterns leads along the
ceiling, far above the reach of those who would attempt to siphon off its
precious burden of oil.  Ragged scars and deep holes mar the sides of the
tunnels where valueable minerals have been mined or pried away, leaving
the place forlorn and hollow looking.  A worn path of dense bricks covers
the floor, the old mortar holding the paving-stones in place slowly
crumbling away to dust.  A gap in the eastern wall leads to a short, dark
tunnel.
