on either side of a tiny passageway leading south.  Along the eastern
wall runs a seris of tubes bearing the precious oil that keeps the
heavily tarnished, pock-marked lamp alight.  A wide band of peach-colored
quartz frames the doorway leading south to an area that seems perfectly
square; obviously this small chamber wasn't formed by nature alone.  The
