Jail~
A shroud of blackness looms over this small cell, lending it the darkness
of a starless midnight.  No ready means of escape is visible, indeed, it
is only by focusing one's eyes that any details at all within the cell
can be discerned.  Granite boulders have been cut into square blocks and
stacked one upon another to provide a thick, massively solid wall.  A
heavy oak door banded with steel seals off this room from the rest of the
world, letting no vestige of light enter the dusky prison.  Two metal
shutters can barely be made out in the door, for both sets of hinges have
been installed on the outside.  A large rock covered in a rancid matting
of straw doubles as a bed, though the stench emanating from its surface
would make one hard-pressed to get any sleep.
